<item>
            <title>[LU-18175] Enhance Lustre to exploit new shrinker handling</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18175</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently Lustre uses the Linux kernel shrinkers for several subsystems to handle freeing data when the system is under pressure. In newer kernels shrinker specific interface&#160; has been developed that allows one to flush the data related to the shrinker. This is a handy feature and can be applied to the super block shrinker as well which Lustre currently doesn&apos;t do any special handling.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Information on this new interface can be found here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://lwn.net/Articles/896274&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lwn.net/Articles/896274&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.kernel.org/admin-guide/mm/shrinker_debugfs.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.kernel.org/admin-guide/mm/shrinker_debugfs.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
